Open edX Conference

Once a year, the entire Open edX community gathers together at the Open edX conference, which is held at a different location each year. There are many purposes for this conference. One is knowledge-sharing: engineers, learning designers, product designers, pedagogical experts, and many more deliver fascinating and engaging talks on a variety of subjects (these talks can be found on our YouTube page). Another is simply meeting one another in-person; the community is distributed all over the world, but it's amazing to see each other in person sometimes and talk, laugh, and get a bite to eat together.

You can follow the conference website, con.openedx.org, where we'll post the latest information about the upcoming conference. 

Sergey Movchan of Raccoon Gang delivers a keynote presentation at Open edX Con 2022 in Lisbon, Portugal
